This square has been converted into a small, rather successful urban park. There are benches in the middle of the vegetation, a little hidden from traffic.
The small square located in front of the library has been very pleasantly converted into a pleasant garden. A relaxing stop on our journeys, appreciated by doggies for whom grass is rare in Paris.

What a great discovery this little park is! Previously a concrete slab, it was recently transformed to make way for a small haven of tranquility, greenery and freshness. Great for a walk with the dog or some quiet time.
The green space is always pleasant but we cannot say that the interest of this little garden is very advanced...

Here in the 4th arrondissement of Paris, remains of the 8 Bastille towers were found, which under Cardinal Richelieu indicated the location where the St. Antoine city gate of the 1st Paris defense belt was under Charles V. Remnants of this belt were found during the construction of the first metro line between Vincennes and today's Place d'Etoile. Nice little green park near the Arsenal.
